  "claim_short": "1208.4762 Dales Question (II) / DalesQ1 for E=c_0\\oplus\\ell_\\infty: every finitely-generated maximal left ideal of B(c_0\\oplus\\ell_\\infty) is fixed. Proof: a non-fixed finitely-generated maximal left ideal contains F(E), hence its finite generator map is bounded below; since c_0\\oplus\\ell_\\infty is isomorphic to finite powers, it contains a bounded-below operator. The strong dichotomy gives inessential operators...",
